content.description: Begin on semi-grody rock, but once you clear the first bulge, the quality drastically improves and turns into beautiful stone with odd features. Follow the semi-sidewinding bolts, and enjoy the puzzling crux up high. This is a fun one.
content.location: It is right of the distinct cliff's edge boulder and left of the grungy crack system that bisects the wall.

content.description: Trick-Or-Teeter is a varied slab route that finished on a wonderfully Halloween-colored bulge. It increases in difficulty the higher one goes, but the moves are well-protected.
content.location: It is the furthest rightmost line of the wall - beneath a rust colored face 30' up.

content.description: Tree Trimmer is a straightforward, low angle, slab climb. The stone is of good quality, and the belay station offers nice shade on toasty days.
content.location: On the right half of the wall, begin in a small alcove between 2 small evergreens.

content.description:
This is a tricky line with holds that are a challenge to find. It has fun and puzzling moves for the grade.

To access the toprope anchors for

Line of Little Resistance

and

Tree Trimmer

, top out on the cliff, and head up and left. There will be 2 tan hangers on top of a protrusion.
content.protection: 4 bolts to anchors. You can access the TR anchors for the 2 climbs to the left.
content.location: On the far right end of Teeter, begin on a small ledge with a steep drop on your right.

content.description: Line of Little Resistance is a low angle jug haul. It is fun but slightly dirty. As the name implies, this is pretty cruiser and gets easier the more in the crack you get. It is good for kids.
content.protection:
A toprope from the anchors above

Tree Trimmer

.
content.location: Stay just right of the grungy crack system that bisects the wall.

content.description: Harris Teeter is another 10 Mile slab route, but it has sustained moves throughout. This ends with a tricky bulge on some zebra-aesthetic rock. It is a homage to my favorite southern grocery store.
content.location:
Start on the same small belay ledge just right of

Trick-Or-Teeter

, on the left end of Teeter Top.

content.description: Scramble up to a ledge for the first clip. It is slightly high, but is on solid 3rd class terrain. Good footwork and loose hips will make quick work of this quality line. Don't worry about the boulder plummeting on your head, Dionysus isn't pulling a fast one on you.
content.location: It is directly beneath the imposing boulder that looks like it could crush you at any time.

content.description: Craterade is a very laid back route on heavily featured slab. This begins on odd stone craters that aren't quite jugs and turns into low angle slab.
content.location:
Begin beneath the big cliffside boulder, and stay 7-ish feet right of

Damocles

.
